{
  "id": "feature-perf-010-websocket-event-optimization",
  "title": "WebSocket Event Batching, Throttling, and Compression",
  "category": "Performance",
  "description": "## Problem\nDuring active AI agent execution, the server emits dozens of WebSocket events per second without batching, throttling, or compression. Each event is individually JSON-serialized and sent. The client processes each event immediately, causing render thrashing. Auto-mode-service alone has 45+ emit calls, and streaming updates fire on every text chunk.\n\n## Current Behavior\n\n### Server - No Event Batching (index.ts lines 401-408):\n```typescript\nif (ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n  const message = JSON.stringify({ type, payload });\n  ws.send(message);  // Every event sent immediately, no batching\n}\n```\n\n### Server - No Throttling on High-Frequency Events:\n`auto-mode-service.ts` emits `auto_mode_progress` events on every AI agent text chunk (lines 897, 1262, 1826, 2571, 2578, 2589, 2996, 3167, 3289, 3329). During active execution, this can be 10-50 events per second.\n\n### Server - No WebSocket Compression (index.ts line 321):\n```typescript\nconst wss = new WebSocketServer({ noServer: true });\n// No perMessageDeflate option - compression disabled\n```\n\n### Client - Limited Debouncing:\n- `use-auto-mode.ts` (lines 264-272): Updates state on EVERY `auto_mode_progress` event\n- `use-electron-agent.ts` (lines 279-310): Sets messages state on EVERY `stream` event\n- `use-board-features.ts` (lines 459-465): Has some debouncing (500ms) for task progress, but other events trigger immediate full re-fetches\n\n### Client - Full Re-fetches on Events:\n`use-board-features.ts` (lines 473-534): Many event types trigger `loadFeatures()` which does a full API re-fetch:\n```typescript\nif (event.type === 'auto_mode_feature_complete') {\n  loadFeatures();  // Full re-fetch\n} else if (event.type === 'plan_approval_required') {\n  loadFeatures();  // Full re-fetch\n} else if (event.type === 'pipeline_step_started') {\n  loadFeatures();  // Full re-fetch\n}\n```\n\n## Required Changes\n\n### Server-Side\n1. **Enable WebSocket compression** in `index.ts`:\n   ```typescript\n   const wss = new WebSocketServer({\n     noServer: true,\n     perMessageDeflate: { zlibDeflateOptions: { level: 6 }, threshold: 1024 }\n   });\n   ```\n2. **Add event throttling** in `lib/events.ts` for high-frequency event types:\n   - `auto_mode_progress`: Max 5 events/second (200ms throttle)\n   - `auto_mode_tool`: Max 10 events/second (100ms throttle)\n   - `auto_mode_feature_complete`, `auto_mode_error`, `plan_approval_required`: Never throttle (critical events)\n3. **Add event batching**: Buffer events in a 50-100ms window, send as a batch\n4. **Reduce payload sizes**: Truncate `content` in progress events more aggressively, omit `projectPath` from events when it can be inferred\n\n### Client-Side\n5. **Throttle streaming UI updates** in `use-electron-agent.ts`:\n   - Use `requestAnimationFrame` to limit `setMessages` to 60fps max during streaming\n6. **Batch activity log updates** in `use-auto-mode.ts`:\n   - Debounce `addAutoModeActivity` calls by 200ms during high-frequency events\n7. **Replace full re-fetches with incremental updates** in `use-board-features.ts`:\n   - On `auto_mode_feature_complete`: Update the specific feature's status in-place instead of re-fetching all\n   - On `pipeline_step_started`: Update the specific feature's pipeline state in-place\n   - Keep full re-fetch as fallback for unknown event types\n8. **Replace session polling with WebSocket events** in `session-manager.tsx` (lines 101-113):\n   - Currently polls every 3s with HTTP requests for each session\n   - Subscribe to `agent:stream` events instead of polling\n\n## Files to Modify\n- `apps/server/src/index.ts` (line 321) - Enable WebSocket compression\n- `apps/server/src/lib/events.ts` - Add event throttling and batching\n- `apps/server/src/services/auto-mode-service.ts` - Reduce payload sizes in progress events\n- `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-auto-mode.ts` - Debounce activity log updates\n- `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-electron-agent.ts` - Throttle stream updates with rAF\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/hooks/use-board-features.ts` - Replace full re-fetches with incremental updates\n- `apps/ui/src/components/session-manager.tsx` - Replace polling with event subscription\n\n## Expected Impact\n- 60-80% reduction in WebSocket messages during active agent execution\n- 40-60% bandwidth reduction with compression\n- Smoother UI during AI agent streaming (no render thrashing)\n- Eliminated polling for session status (3s interval HTTP requests removed)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- WebSocket messages show Content-Encoding in devtools\n- During agent execution, message rate is throttled (verify in WS frame inspector)\n- UI remains smooth during heavy streaming (no jank, 60fps scrolling)\n- Critical events (error, complete, plan approval) are never delayed\n- Session running state updates via WebSocket instead of polling\n- Board view updates incrementally instead of full re-fetch on most events\n\n## Reference\n- Existing resize throttling pattern in `index.ts` (line 431): `RESIZE_MIN_INTERVAL_MS`\n- Existing debounce in `use-board-features.ts` (lines 459-465): `debouncedReloadForTaskProgress`",
